sugary beverages,
or cereal, or stuff

00:34:38.889 --> 00:34:42.179
like that, that brand
should probably not

00:34:42.179 --> 00:34:45.170
try to reposition itself
as a healthy brand,

00:34:45.170 --> 00:34:47.679
because the consumer is
not going to trust it.

00:34:47.679 --> 00:34:50.739
A brand that does that and
tries to proclaim itself

00:34:50.739 --> 00:34:52.219
to be something
else, you probably

00:34:52.219 --> 00:34:54.389
will actually hurt
the parent brand

00:34:54.389 --> 00:34:55.792
because it will
seem unauthentic.

00:34:55.792 --> 00:34:57.250
So I think the most
important thing

00:34:57.250 --> 00:34:59.550
is to be authentic,
to understand

00:34:59.550 --> 00:35:02.740
what is it that you are, and
what does your core consumer

00:35:02.740 --> 00:35:03.240
care about.

00:35:03.240 --> 00:35:05.360
And then do that
for your consumer.

00:35:05.360 --> 00:35:09.550
And then if you're
a gigantic company

00:35:09.550 --> 00:35:12.030
and you feel that you need
to go in a another category,

00:35:12.030 --> 00:35:16.300
sometimes it's better to just
acquire or start a new brand

00:35:16.300 --> 00:35:18.940
than to have a brand
that has negative equity

00:35:18.940 --> 00:35:20.960
in the particular place
where you want to go.

00:35:20.960 --> 00:35:24.600
But I don't believe that you
need to go to all places.

00:35:24.600 --> 00:35:28.830
I've seen a lot of friends at
other companies say, oh wow.

00:35:28.830 --> 00:35:30.560
Right now the hot
thing is organic.

00:35:30.560 --> 00:35:32.436
And oh wow, right
now it's gluten free.

00:35:32.436 --> 00:35:34.310
And then they come up
with gluten free salsa.

00:35:34.310 --> 00:35:35.070
Well yeah.

00:35:35.070 --> 00:35:40.080
Salsa is gluten free because
it doesn't have gluten.

00:35:40.080 --> 00:35:44.655
But consumers are very
sophisticated in the end

00:35:44.655 --> 00:35:45.190
of the day.

00:35:45.190 --> 00:35:47.700
You can actually fool
them once or twice,

00:35:47.700 --> 00:35:49.650
but in the longer
term, in the mid-term,

00:35:49.650 --> 00:35:51.089
they're going to figure it out.

00:35:51.089 --> 00:35:52.630
So I think you need
to really, really

00:35:52.630 --> 00:35:55.600
be authentic and understand
what your brand stands for,

00:35:55.600 --> 00:35:57.870
and have a conversation
with your own consumers

00:35:57.870 --> 00:35:59.760
and with yourself,
and then figure out

00:35:59.760 --> 00:36:02.510
how to deliver to
them what that is.

00:36:02.510 --> 00:36:04.770
Again, in the
cereal space, there

00:36:04.770 --> 00:36:08.285
are so many opportunities
within that brand equity,

00:36:08.285 --> 00:36:11.890
I just would try to stay there.

00:36:11.890 --> 00:36:14.810
Fortunately, I don't have to
answer that question for real.

00:36:14.810 --> 00:36:18.490
[? Because ?] there are $60
billion dollar companies,

00:36:18.490 --> 00:36:20.870
$100 billion companies that
have a lot of these legacy

00:36:20.870 --> 00:36:21.990
challenges.

00:36:21.990 --> 00:36:22.892
And it's not easy.

00:36:22.892 --> 00:36:24.850
And a lot of the people
leading these companies

00:36:24.850 --> 00:36:27.410
are formidable
good human beings,

00:36:27.410 --> 00:36:30.370
they're just inheriting
these challenges.

00:36:30.370 --> 00:36:33.195
And it's not easy.

